<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB04573</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT ESTABLISHING A NATIONAL ECONOMIC DECENTRALIZATION PLAN TO FACILITATE FURTHER GROWTH IN ALL REGIONS OF THE PHILIPPINES AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : "The Progresibong Pilipinas Para sa Lahat ng Pilipino Act"
Aims to create a more progressive Philippines for every Filipino through:
a) Comprehensive studies focusing on challenges and opportunities for regional economic development;
b) Phil. Healthcare Development Program which shall include establishment of specialty hospitals such as Phil.   Heart Center, Lung Center of the Phils. National Kidney and Transplant Inst. and Phil. Orthopedic Center;
c) Regional Centers for Excellence Development Program focusing on education and skills development;
d) Relocation of NGAs to ensure effective and efficient communication and coordination between and among them, enhancing delivery of public goods and services in the regions/countryside;
e) Regional decentralization mechanisms of procurement procedures for major NGA projects; 
f) Tax incentives for industries locating outside NCR.
</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>RODRIGUEZ, RUFUS B.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2019-09-12</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON ECONOMIC AFFAIRS ON 2019-09-16</td></tr></table>